{% if extraction_target == "entities" %}
Extract entities from the corroboration document page, following the ontology exactly.

ENTITY ONTOLOGY:
{% for e in entity_ontology_rich %}
  Type        : {{ e.type }}
  Description : {{ e.description }}
  label       : write a short human-readable summary of this entity (e.g. "John Smith", "Alpine Bank savings account", "CHF 50k transfer to GlobalTech")
  Attributes  : {{ e.attributes | tojson }}
{% endfor %}

ENTITIES ALREADY IN THE GRAPH (cumulative — history + previous corroboration documents):
{{ known_entities | tojson(indent=2) }}

TASK:
1. For each entity mentioned in the page, check if it already exists in the list above
   by matching on name, alias, label, or key attributes. Use exact AND partial/fuzzy matching.
2. If it matches an existing entity → add its ID to "reused_ids". Do NOT re-extract it.
3. If it is genuinely new (not in the list) → add it to "new_entities".

DOCUMENT SUMMARY:
{{ document_summary }}

PAGE {{ page_number }} SUMMARY:
{{ page_summary }}

Return:
{
  "reused_ids": [
    "<id of existing entity from the graph that appears on this page>"
  ],
  "new_entities": [
    {
      "id": "<placeholder — will be replaced automatically>",
      "type": "<entity type from ontology>",
      "label": "<concise human-readable description>",
      "attributes": {
        "<every attribute for this type>": "<value or null>"
      }
    }
  ],
  "entities_to_remove": []
}

Rules:
- "reused_ids" must only contain IDs that exist verbatim in the known entities list above.
- "new_entities" must only contain entities with NO match in the known entities list.
- Use ONLY ontology-defined types and attributes for new entities.
- Every attribute must appear for new entities — use null if not found.
- Do not invent values.

{% else %}
Extract relationships from the corroboration document page, following the ontology exactly.

RELATIONSHIP ONTOLOGY — for each type the exact attributes to include are listed:
{% for r in relationship_ontology_rich %}
{{ r.type }}:
  {
    "type": "{{ r.type }}",
    "source": "<id of a {{ r.from | join(' or ') }} entity>",
    "target": "<id of a {{ r.to | join(' or ') }} entity>",
    "attributes": {
      "evidence": "<verbatim or paraphrased quote from document>",
      {% if r.attributes is mapping %}{% for attr in r.attributes.keys() %}"{{ attr }}": "<value or null>"{% if not loop.last %},
      {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% endif %}

    }
  }
{% endfor %}

ALL AVAILABLE ENTITIES (use their exact IDs as source/target):
{{ known_entities | tojson(indent=2) }}

DOCUMENT SUMMARY:
{{ document_summary }}

PAGE {{ page_number }} SUMMARY:
{{ page_summary }}

Return:
{
  "relationships": [ ... one object per relationship found, using the structure shown above for each type ... ],
  "relationships_to_remove": []
}

Rules:
- Use ONLY ontology-defined relationship types.
- source/target must match the allowed From/To entity types.
- Include ONLY the attribute keys shown for the specific relationship type plus "evidence".
- Every listed attribute must appear — use null if not found.
- "evidence" is REQUIRED — never leave it empty.
- Do NOT include a "reasoning" field.
- You may link history KG entities to new corroboration entities.
{% endif %}
